BP Solar, a unit of energy giant BP, will construct a groundbreaking solar plant in Alentejo, creating 240 jobs.
With 350,000 solar panels spread over 114 hectares near Moura, the plant will produce 62 megawatts, surpassing Germany's largest station.
Construction starts in 2006, as Portugal aims to meet renewable energy targets under the Kyoto Protocol.
Meanwhile, solar-powered car races in Australia showcase innovative technology.
In the Philippines, a solar power project funded by Spain will benefit rural communities.
Taiwan also shows promise in solar energy development, emphasizing the need for a complete supply chain.
